KLM Royal Dutch Airlines &lt;KLM.AS>, ina move following similar steps recently by U.S. carrier TWA,said it is cutting its fares on transatlantic flights fromApril 1.    From April 1, a return fare Amsterdam-New York will be cutby eight per cent to 1,099 guilders for the low season untilmid-June, when seasonal increases will come into effect.    KLM recently rejected invitations by TWA to coordinateprice cuts on the Amsterdam route and a spokesman said KLM hadonly moved now to start up a nationwide promotional campaign inthe Netherlands to boost travel to the U.S. Reuter&#3;